   The Second Congressional District | District Info | Local Government |
                                Site Index |


     Utah's Second Congressional District is a compact district
     comprising the thirteen cities of Draper, Sandy, Bluffdale,
     Riverton, South Jordan, West Jordan, Holladay, Midvale, Murray,
     Kearns, Taylorsville, South Salt Lake and Salt Lake City.  According
     to the 2000 US Census, there are currently 702,102 residents in the
     district.  To learn more about the cities in Utah's Second District,
     click here.  You can also find out more about the
     district's business, educational and cultural opportunities by
     clicking here.  To see a map of where the Second Congressional
     District is in Salt Lake County, click here.

